Package xxl.spatial

Support and building-blocks for spatial, temporal, similarity algorithms and data types.

Interface Summary

Descriptable A class is Descriptable if it can be described by a Descriptor.

AsciiKPEConverter An AsciiKPEConverter can be used to convert KPE-Objects that are stored in ASCII-format to a binary representation.
FixedPointRectangle A Rectangle that uses an internal fixed-point representation.
FloatPoint A Wrapper for float[]-points that provides useful methods on points like for example the lp-metric.
FloatPointInputIterator The FloatPointInputIterator constructs an Iterator for a given File of FloatPoint-Objects.
KPE A key-pointer-element aggregates a Descriptor and an ID.

KPEKPEzCodeMapper Maps a KPE to a KPEzCode.

KPEs A collections of useful methods for dealing with spatial data.
KPEzCode A KPE + zCode.
NestedLoops NestedLoops intersection-join for Descriptable-Objects.

Overlaps A binary Predicate that returns true if two descriptors overlap.
PointEpsilonRectangleMapper Maps a point to a rectangle where point is the center of a rectangle 2*epsilon x 2*epsilon x ...

Replicator Maps a KPE to an Iterator of KPEzCode-Objects.
Replicator.MaxGeneration Allows at most bound generations (2^generation replicates are created).
Replicator.MaxReplicates Constrains replication to replicates per input-element
Replicator.MaxSplitBit Allows splits if the bitIndex is smaller or equal than a given bitIndex.
Replicator.MaxSplitLevel Allows splits if the level is smaller or equal than a given level.
Replicator.MaxSplitsPerLevel Allows at most bound splits per level.
Replicator.QueueEl Wrapper-class needed to unwind the recursive split.
Replicator.Split Abstract Predicate used to decide whether further splits are allowed.
 

Package xxl.spatial Description

Support and building-blocks for spatial, temporal, similarity algorithms and data types. Note, that this package is somewhat experimental! Several algorithms are currently developed and will be integrated in the next official release (Plane Sweep, GESS, Hash-based stuff).
Author: Jens-Peter Dittrich
